  m_GameObject: {fileID: 416974743}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 82ce8022a2244094f8253829acd6f6e6, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  handbookPanel: {fileID: 1833029023}
  pageTitleText: {fileID: 449713856}
  pageBodyText: {fileID: 16200093}
  pageNumberText: {fileID: 1066350898}
  previousButton: {fileID: 804629622}
  nextButton: {fileID: 205704250}
  pages:
  - title: Welcome to the Post Office
    body: 'Welcome to the Hiraya Town Post Office.



      Our town may be small,
      but every letter that passes through this room carries a small part of someone''s
      day.



      Take your time, read carefully, and help every piece of mail
      find its way home.'
  - title: A Day Behind the Desk
    body: 'Each morning begins with a fresh stack of letters and parcels.



      Look
      over each item before placing it with the day''s deliveries. Names, addresses,
      handwriting, stickers, and other markings may all help you understand where
      it belongs.



      There is no need to rush. Care is more important than
      speed.'
  - title: Names Are Not Always Simple
    body: 'People are sometimes known by more than one name.



      A letter may
      use a nickname, an old surname, a username, or only a person''s initials.



      When
      something seems unfamiliar, the Hiraya Town Resident Directory may contain
      the clue you need.'
  - title: When Mail Cannot Be Delivered
    body: 'Some mail may carry an incomplete address, an old address, or another
      problem that prevents normal delivery.



      Parcels should be placed in
      the package area when they require separate handling.



      Mail that cannot
      continue to its destination belongs in the outgoing and return tray.'
